properties.areaDesc: South Laramie Range Foothills; Central Carbon County; South Laramie Range
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 7 at 2:03PM MST until February 8 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...SIGNIFICANT TRAVEL IMPACTS WILL PERSIST ALONG AND WEST OF THE
LARAMIE RANGE THROUGH AT LEAST SATURDAY MORNING...

* WHAT...Occasional snow and blowing snow. Additional snow
accumulations of one to two inches. Winds gusting as high as 40
mph.

* WHERE...Central Carbon County, South Laramie Range and South
Laramie Range Foothills.

* WHEN...Until 5 AM MST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel will be difficult due to icy, snow covered
roads and periods of low visibility in falling and blowing
snow.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
